headline: Regeneron to acquire bankrupt genetic tester 23andMe
summary: Regeneron Pharmaceutical (REGN) is buying 23andMe’s (MEHCQ) genetics business out of bankruptcy for $256 million, aiming to boost its drug discovery capabilities using DNA data. Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Anjalee Khemlani explains how the deal ties into Regeneron’s broader strategy and addresses privacy concerns. headline: Biotechnology company Regeneron buying 23andMe for $256 million
summary: Biotechnology company Regeneron Pharmaceuticals is buying 23andMe for $256 million, two months after the genetic testing company filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection.  In March 23andMe said that it was looking to sell “substantially all of its assets” through a court-approved reorganization plan.  Its co-founder and CEO Anne Wojcicki also resigned from the top post, but remained as a board member.
